  "body": "Please see https://github.com/roboll/helmfile/issues/149 for more information, but at a very high level it'd be great if when `helm install --namespace` results in a namespace being created, if that namespace gets created before helm attempts to execute the command, and results in a `namespace already exists`, helm shouldn't really fail.\r\n\r\nThis is replicated via concurrency of running two `helm install --namespace <thing>` at the same time, for the same namespace, that doesn't already exist.\r\n",
